Text.Value: Attack the dwarf.
I wonder what they'll think when I bring them the hand cut from your corpse?
Long may he reign.
So you're the one who's been murdering people. Your killings end here.
I know you... and you are most certainly not a faithful of Bhaal. Not like I am.
I'm going to obliterate this so-called 'Tribunal'. Why not help me? They will rue the day they spurned you in Bhaal's name.

As sure as setting of the sun,
Thine Unholy will be done.
That this 'Tribunal' would pit two perfect killers against each other shows it does not serve Bhaal. We should destroy it.
If you want it that much, don't let me stop you.
I think you are confused, wraith. You speak of another. Who has proven themselves like me? Who has sacrificed what I have? SPEAK!
Your ascension isn't happening. I already killed Sarevok, and the rest of the tribunal.
I find this dwarf tiresome. It should be disposed of.
Don't get angry - you can polish the Unholy Assassin's boots if you want!
That title is mine. That you would give it to some indolent civilian is an affront.
I heard that there was another aspirant seeking the Tribunal.
Bhaal is a god of murder, not manners. Besides, you would call this weakling my 'better'? Ridiculous.
I don't care enough to fight you for it. Go ahead.
I knew I should have killed you the last time we met.
He is the Lord of Murder. Let us remind the Tribunal of this.

Such weak will dost no Bhaalist make.
This life, young dwarf, is thine to take.
I'll give you a choice. Either help me crush this pathetic tribute to Bhaal, or die.
You're... you're right. Bhaal is not a god of decrees and doctrines.

The ground doth shake, the air is thin.
Hail, Unholy Assassin.
Fine, I will add this pretender to my many sacrifices in Bhaal's name. May it please the Tribunal.

Though folly most unusual,
Just one may seek the Tribunal.
Attack.
You're right. It's me. I'm the Unholy Assassin. Would you like a demonstration?
Joining forces is the most strategic course of action. Why don't we take down this 'Tribunal' together?
You're the one who's been murdering the targets from the list! Too bad you were too late to claim the prize.

We are approached, so still thy rant.
Share you shall in murder's chant.
Who is this? Some worthless imitator, no doubt. A forgery.
You again? I knew I should have killed you last time we met.
But there can only be one Unholy Assassin. If you think you're getting in the way of my ascension, you are deeply mistaken.

Thou speakest not with reverent zeal -
I'll still thy tongue with Bhaalist steel.

Of thy betters speak not ill.
Thus demands our Lord Bhaal's will.
I'll rip that smarmy tongue out of your head.
You can have the title, I'll just leave.
You're the one who's been murdering the targets from the list! Too bad you were too late to claim the prize.
No. I will cut the hand from your heretical corpse and bring it before the Tribunal. I will ascend.
The Murder Tribunal seemed to think I was pretty good.

Synopsis: Dialog with the Death Knight sentry guarding the courtroom of the Murder Tribunal, in an underground area beneath Baldur's Gate. If you know that this is where you become an Unholy Assassin - and you have a victim's hand with you - he will let you through to be judged by the tribunal.
